# MOC - The Fourth Search

## The Problem
- [[the-context-bottleneck]] - a million tokens of content, the AI starts knowing nothing
- [[context-is-the-differentiator]] - outsized value comes from solving the context problem
- [[optimising-context-for-ai]] - getting the right 5-10 notes without burning the window

## The Four Modalities
- [[four-modalities-of-search]] - the framework: keyword, metadata, graph, semantic
- [[keyword-search]] - finds what you said, a targeting mechanism for tokens
- [[metadata-search]] - finds what you filed, human indexing that became a query layer
- [[the-link-graph]] - finds what you connected, deliberate human judgement
- [[semantic-search]] - finds what you meant, the fourth that multiplied three

## The Compounding Effects
- [[chaining-search-modalities]] - keyword to semantic, semantic to metadata, graph to semantic
- [[the-flywheel]] - more links, richer traversals, richer context, more connections
- [[human-judgement-vs-machine-understanding]] - the delta between graph and semantic is where the signal lives
- [[the-ai-surfaces-connections-you-missed]] - the network gets richer through collaboration

## The Philosophy
- [[thinking-residue]] - rich retrieval grows from people doing real work inside the system
- [[build-systems-people-think-inside]] - working environments, not retrieval databases
- [[the-best-knowledge-layer-is-a-working-environment]] - retrieval as byproduct of thinking
- [[the-context-layer]] - persistent, decoupled, owned
- [[compound-interest-on-thinking]] - every interaction enriches the layer
- [[links-do-the-work]] - each link is a deliberate assertion of connection

